collections.name: Mimosa
collections.description: Algorithmically generated, Mimosa reflects affective experiences through pulse-like wavy lines, structured within grids of 16, 24, or 36 cells. The algorithm relies on a limited palette of core colors: black, white, red, green and blue. Perlin noise defines the angle and distortion of each curve. Extra colors are assigned in select compositions to areas of lower resistance, determined by waviness values, enhancing the distinction of stroke patterns.

collections.name: Zombies - Eaters of Flesh
collections.description:
"Zombies – Eaters of Flesh" might just be the most grotesquely unapologetic NFT collection to ever claw its way onto the blockchain. A digital fever dream of malformed pixels, this collection proudly embraces its hideousness, shunning aesthetic appeal in favor of pure, undiluted revulsion. Each NFT in the set resembles something between a decomposed potato and a glitchy 8-bit horror movie still, with jagged teeth, asymmetrical eyeballs, and color palettes that look like a toddler’s finger painting after a sugar crash. There’s no polish, no subtlety—just rotting, chaotic carnage rendered in low-resolution misery.

What makes "Zombies – Eaters of Flesh" stand out isn’t just its commitment to being ugly—it’s the almost philosophical boldness in that ugliness. collections.name: TEST1 & NOT ACTIVE
collections.description:
Not a battle of right vs. wrong. Not truth vs. lies. This is about the human experience of perception and choice.

A 23 items 1/1 series (that partners with a 4 items 1/1 special series).

We pour effort into something—relationships, ambitions, even daily tasks—but reality doesn’t always align with what we envisioned. Fatigue sets in, expectations bend, and at some point, we adjust, reinterpret, or outright deny. We tell ourselves “it’s fine” when we know it’s not. We look the other way. We balance between truth and denial, sometimes embracing reality, sometimes rewriting it.

Denial isn’t just avoidance—it’s a tool. A pause. A coping mechanism. Sometimes it buys time, sometimes it holds us back. This Timecoin is a mirror of that universal moment—the inner conflict, the decision to see or unsee, the choice to move forward or stay in limbo.

The open eye sees. The closed eye chooses not to. Truth and denial are two sides of the same coin set in time, in our own key moment of the day.

collections.name: Seed
collections.description:
Seed is a series of images that visualize the latent noise tensor generated by Stable Diffusion using manual seeds starting from 0.
Each image represents the unprocessed input from which an AI-generated image could emerge.
It is not the result of sampling or decoding, but a direct projection of the model’s initial noise state into visible form.

Latent noise tensors, visualized
Generated via PyTorch 1.13.1
Tensor shape: [1, 4, 64, 64]
Values drawn from: 𝒩(0, 1)
Random generator: Mersenne Twister (manual seed)
Visualization: Weighted RGB mapping from latent tensor via fixed linear transformation (L1–L4 → RGB), followed by normalization to [0, 1]
Resolution: 64×64 px
